# Tight harness rules

- Only modify code required by the task; no unrelated refactors or files.
- Read surrounding code first; match existing naming, types, and patterns.
- Reuse existing functions and components instead of reimplementing.
- Do not add markdown docs unless asked.
- Never commit or write secrets (`.env`, keys, credentials).
- Verify with `npm run typecheck` and `npm test` after substantive edits.
